    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-19T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-19T07:00:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115A European War/9–1944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-19T13:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 19, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 1910 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3725. Department’s 1866, September 18, 3 p.m. One Allied airman will be
                    immediately released for each German soldier of whatever category who may be
                    brought here aboard Finnish vessel or who may cross Swedish frontier. German
                    will be offered choice of remaining in Sweden or returning to Germany but
                    release of Allied airman will not be affected in the event German chooses to
                    remain in Sweden. I regret that foregoing was not made clear in my 3708,
                    September 18, 2 p.m.<note n="66" xml:id="d639fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
